text: Coudekerque-Village is a former commune in Nord in north France. In 2019, 1,380 people lived there. On 1 January 2016, it was merged into the new commune of Téteghem-Coudekerque-Village.Arrêté préfectoral 30 November 2015 == References == Category:Former communes in Nord
title: Coudekerque-Village
